document_metadata.name: Anti-inflammatory activity of anatabine via inhibition of STAT3 phosphorylation

links.evidence: Nicotine has been shown to modulate inflammation by affecting STAT3 phosphorylation (Chatterjee et al., 2009; Hosur and Loring, 2011) and by opposing NFkB activation (Leite et al., 2010; Zhou et al., 2010)
